

Monefy Mobile App Automation
Android UI Automation Framework (Appium 8 + Java 17 + TestNG + Maven)
This repository contains a complete mobile automation framework for the Monefy Lite Android application.
It demonstrates modern Appium 8.x practices, clean architecture, and real world problem solving ‚Äî including handling UI elements that do not expose locators on Android 14.
The project is structured to be scalable, and easy to maintain.
________________________________________
Features
Modern Appium 8.x (W3C Actions, no deprecated APIs)
Appium 8 removed TouchAction, MobileElement, and other legacy APIs.
This framework uses Selenium 4 W3C Actions for gestures.
Clean Page Object Model (POM)
Each screen is represented as a dedicated class under com.d.monefy.screens.
Reusable BaseScreen
Provides:
‚Ä¢	click()
‚Ä¢	type()
‚Ä¢	id()
‚Ä¢	xpath()
‚Ä¢	tapByPercentage() (W3C coordinate tap)
Coordinate based tap for the Floating Action Button (+)
On Android 14, the Monefy Lite FAB does not expose a resource id in the UI hierarchy.
Appium Inspector and UIAutomator do not show the element.
To ensure reliable automation, the framework uses a percentage based coordinate tap:
tapByPercentage(0.50, 0.88);
This approach is:
‚Ä¢	Resolution independent
‚Ä¢	Emulator agnostic
‚Ä¢	Stable across Android versions
End to end flows
Includes flows for:
‚Ä¢	Adding income
‚Ä¢	Adding expense
‚Ä¢	Performing transfers
