Environment Setup
1. Install Android Studio
‚Ä¢	Install Android Studio Flamingo or newer
‚Ä¢	Install SDK Platform 34 (Android 14)
‚Ä¢	Install: 
o	Android SDK Tools
o	Android SDK Platform Tools
o	Android Emulator
2. Create an Android Emulator
Recommended configuration:
Setting	Value
Device	Pixel 6a / Pixel 7
Android Version	14
Play Store	Enabled
RAM	2‚Äì4 GB
Start the emulator before running tests.
________________________________________
üîç Appium Inspector Setup
1.	Install Appium Inspector
2.	Start Appium Server manually:
appium --port 4723
3.	Use these capabilities:
{
  "platformName": "Android",
  "appium:automationName": "UiAutomator2",
  "appium:deviceName": "emulator-5554",
  "appium:platformVersion": "14",
  "appium:appPackage": "com.monefy.app.lite",
  "appium:appActivity": "com.monefy.activities.main.MainActivity_",
  "appium:noReset": true
}
Some Monefy builds use MainActivity or MainActivityAlias.
Confirm via:
adb shell dumpsys window | findstr mCurrentFocus
________________________________________
 The + Button Locator Issue (Real World Problem)
On Android 14, the Monefy Lite floating action button (FAB) does not expose any locator:
‚Ä¢	No resource-id
‚Ä¢	No content-desc
‚Ä¢	No text
‚Ä¢	Not visible in Appium Inspector
‚Ä¢	Not visible in UIAutomator dump
Result
All tests depending on tapping the + button failed.
________________________________________
Solution: Coordinate Based Tap (W3C Actions)
To bypass the missing locator, the framework uses a percentage based tap:
tapByPercentage(0.50, 0.88);
This reliably opens the radial menu on all emulator sizes.
Why this works
‚Ä¢	FAB is always centered horizontally
‚Ä¢	FAB is always above the bottom navigation
‚Ä¢	Percentage based taps scale across devices
________________________________________
Driver Creation Failure & Skipped Tests (Important Note)
During development, a known issue occurred:
ClientConfig(...) constructor mismatch
Driver session not created
Tests skipped
 Root Cause
Appium 8.x requires Selenium 4.20.0.
Any other Selenium version causes driver creation failure.
Fix
Explicitly set:
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.seleniumhq.selenium</groupId>
    <artifactId>selenium-java</artifactId>
    <version>4.20.0</version>
</dependency>
Why tests were skipped
If the driver fails in @BeforeClass, TestNG marks all tests as skipped.
Allure also shows them as skipped.
________________________________________
Running Tests
mvn clean test
________________________________________
Viewing Allure Report
After running tests:
allure serve target/allure-results
This generates and opens the report automatically.
________________________________________ Dependencies
<dependency>
    <groupId>io.appium</groupId>
    <artifactId>java-client</artifactId>
    <version>8.5.1</version>
</dependency>

<dependency>
    <groupId>org.seleniumhq.selenium</groupId>
    <artifactId>selenium-java</artifactId>
    <version>4.20.0</version>
</dependency>
________________________________________
Known Limitations
1. Floating Action Button (+)
No locator available on Android 14.
Framework uses coordinate based tap.
2. AppActivity differences
Different app versions may use:
‚Ä¢	MainActivity_
‚Ä¢	MainActivity
‚Ä¢	MainActivityAlias
3. Driver creation may fail if:
‚Ä¢	Wrong Selenium version
‚Ä¢	Wrong AppActivity
‚Ä¢	Emulator not fully booted
‚Ä¢	Appium server not running
4. Skipped tests
If driver fails in setup, TestNG marks all tests as skipped.
